text: Eleutheria is an ancient and modern Greek term for, and personification of, liberty. Eleutheria may also refer to: * Eleutheria (Hydrozoa), a genus of hydrozoans * Eleutheria (play), a posthumously published play by Samuel Beckett * "Eleutheria", a song by Jason Webley from the 1999 album Against the Night * "Eleutheria", a song by Lenny Kravitz from the 1993 album Are You Gonna Go My Way * Eleutheria, a student co-operative at Michigan State University; see Student Housing Cooperative at Michigan State University ==See also== * Eleuthera, an island in the Bahamas * Eleutherion, an ancient Byzantine port near Istanbul, Turkey
title: Eleutheria (disambiguation)
